mibtermSrvProfileTable.name: mibtermSrvProfileTable
mibtermSrvProfileTable.description: A list of mibtermSrvProfile profile entries.

mibtermSrvProfileEntry.name: mibtermSrvProfileEntry
mibtermSrvProfileEntry.description: A mibtermSrvProfile entry containing objects that maps to the parameters of mibtermSrvProfile profile.

termSrvProfile_Enabled.name: termSrvProfile_Enabled
termSrvProfile_Enabled.description: Terminal server availability flag. When set to no all terminal server functions are disabled.

termSrvProfile_SecurityMode.name: termSrvProfile_SecurityMode
termSrvProfile_SecurityMode.description: Indicates the type of terminal server security (if any).

termSrvProfile_ModemConfiguration_V42_mn.name: termSrvProfile_ModemConfiguration_V42_mnp
termSrvProfile_ModemConfiguration_V42_mn.description: Describes the modem error correction mode. Error correction can be required, not used, or optional.

termSrvProfile_ModemConfiguration_MaxBau.name: termSrvProfile_ModemConfiguration_MaxBaudRate
termSrvProfile_ModemConfiguration_MaxBau.description: Describes the maximum connection baud rate the modems should try.

termSrvProfile_ModemConfiguration_ModemT.name: termSrvProfile_ModemConfiguration_ModemTransmitLevel
termSrvProfile_ModemConfiguration_ModemT.description: The transmit attenuate level the modems should try.

termSrvProfile_ModemConfiguration_CellMo.name: termSrvProfile_ModemConfiguration_CellModeFirst
termSrvProfile_ModemConfiguration_CellMo.description: If yes, the modem attempts cellular connection first - then land connection. If no, land based is attempted first, then cellular.

termSrvProfile_ModemConfiguration_CellLe.name: termSrvProfile_ModemConfiguration_CellLevel
termSrvProfile_ModemConfiguration_CellLe.description: The modem cellular communications transmit and receive level. Valid values are -10 db .. -18 db.

termSrvProfile_ModemConfiguration_o7Even.name: termSrvProfile_ModemConfiguration_o7Even
termSrvProfile_ModemConfiguration_o7Even.description: If set to yes, all incoming data has its parity bit cleared and all outgoing data is forced to 7 bits with even parity.

termSrvProfile_ModemConfiguration_ModemM.name: termSrvProfile_ModemConfiguration_ModemMod
termSrvProfile_ModemConfiguration_ModemM.description: The modulation protocol to be attempted by the modems.

termSrvProfile_ModemConfiguration_oATAns.name: termSrvProfile_ModemConfiguration_oATAnswerString
termSrvProfile_ModemConfiguration_oATAns.description: Allows the user to enter any additional AT commands in the modem answer string.

termSrvProfile_ModemConfiguration_QuickC.name: termSrvProfile_ModemConfiguration_QuickConnectEnabled
termSrvProfile_ModemConfiguration_QuickC.description: If set to yes, Quick-Connect will be enabled.

termSrvProfile_ModemConfiguration_MaxV92.name: termSrvProfile_ModemConfiguration_MaxV92ReceiveBaudRate
termSrvProfile_ModemConfiguration_MaxV92.description: The maximum V.92 receive baud rate to be attempted by the modems.

termSrvProfile_ModemConfiguration_V44Ena.name: termSrvProfile_ModemConfiguration_V44Enabled
termSrvProfile_ModemConfiguration_V44Ena.description: If set to yes, allow V.44 compression to be negotiated

termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.name: termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration_SilentMode
termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.description: Don't generate any status messages upon connection.

termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.name: termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration_ClearScreen
termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.description: Clear the screen at terminal server startup.

termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.name: termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration_SystemPassword
termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.description: Global terminal server system access password.

termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.name: termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration_Banner
termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.description: The terminal server login banner.

termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.name: termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration_LoginPrompt
termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.description: The string used to prompt for user name when authentication is in use.

termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.name: termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration_PasswordPrompt
termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.description: The string used to prompt for password when authentication is in use.

termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.name: termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration_ThirdLoginPrompt
termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.description: An optional third prompt for a terminal server login. If this value is null no third prompt is used.

termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.name: termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration_ThirdPromptSequence
termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.description: Select where the third prompt should appear in the login sequence: either before or after user name & password.

termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.name: termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration_Prompt
termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.description: The current terminal server prompt.

termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.name: termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration_TerminalType
termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.description: The default terminal type for telnet and rlogin sessions.

termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.name: termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration_ClearCall
termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.description: Select operation when a telnet/rlogin/tcp session terminates. When set to yes, the dial-in session will also terminate.

termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.name: termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration_BufferChars
termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.description: Whether to buffer termserv characters or to forward them without buffering. Buffering provides better throughput at a slight increase in latency.

termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.name: termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration_Ping
termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.description: Enable/disable the ping command from the terminal server.

termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.name: termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration_Traceroute
termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.description: Enable/disable the traceroute command from the terminal server.

termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.name: termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration_Tcp
termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.description: Enable/disable the tcp command from the terminal server.

termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.name: termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration_TsAraEnabled
termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.description: TRUE if terminal server users are allowed to intiate async ARA sessions.

termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.name: termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration_RloginOptions_Rlogin
termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.description: Enable/disable the rlogin command from the terminal server.

termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.name: termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration_RloginOptions_MaxSourcePort
termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.description: A highest limit of the port number used by rlogin. For BSD's rlogin, the client source port range is 512 to 1023.

termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.name: termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration_RloginOptions_MinSourcePort
termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.description: A lowest limit of the port number used by rlogin. For BSD's rlogin, the client source port range is 512 to 1023.

termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.name: termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration_TelnetOptions_Telnet
termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.description: Enable/disable the use of the telnet terminal server command.

termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.name: termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration_TelnetOptions_TelnetMode
termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.description: Selects default Telnet mode: ASCII, Binary, or Transparent.

termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.name: termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration_TelnetOptions_AutoTelnet
termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.description: If set to 'yes' unknown terminal server commands will be treated as the name of a host to telnet to.

termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.name: termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration_TelnetOptions_LocalEcho
termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.description: Defines the default echo mode for telnet sessions. The default mode can be overridded on the command line.

termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.name: termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration_TelnetOptions_Security
termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.description: Level of security used to authenticate telnet sessions.

termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.name: termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration_IpAddMsg
termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.description: This is a text field that will be printed in front of the IP address in the terminal server when going into PPP.

termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.name: termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration_PromptFormat
termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.description: TRUE if the terminal server prompt should interpret \\n.

termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.name: termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration_IpNetmaskMsg
termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.description: This is a text field that will be printed in front of the IP Netmask in the terminal server when going into SLIP.

termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.name: termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration_IpGwAddMsg
termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.description: This is a text field that will be printed in front of the IP Gateway address in the terminal server when going into SLIP.

termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.name: termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration_LoginTimeout
termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.description: The number of seconds to wait at the login prompt for the user to login. A value of 0 disables the timeout.

termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.name: termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration_PacketizeWaitTime
termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.description: The number of milliseconds to accumulate modem data in a packet.

termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.name: termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration_PacketizeChars
termSrvProfile_TerminalModeConfiguration.description: The number of characters to accumulate modem data in a packet.

termSrvProfile_ImmediateModeOptions_Serv.name: termSrvProfile_ImmediateModeOptions_Service
termSrvProfile_ImmediateModeOptions_Serv.description: enable/disable immediate mode and specify the service type. Immediate mode is where a user is automatically connected to a remote host using the specified service.

termSrvProfile_ImmediateModeOptions_Teln.name: termSrvProfile_ImmediateModeOptions_TelnetHostAuth
termSrvProfile_ImmediateModeOptions_Teln.description: Option defines if telnet is started directly bypassing the local authentication process. When enabled, authentication is the responsibility of the telnet host.

termSrvProfile_ImmediateModeOptions_Host.name: termSrvProfile_ImmediateModeOptions_Host
termSrvProfile_ImmediateModeOptions_Host.description: Name or IP address or X.121 address of the immediate TELNET, TCP, or X.25/Pad host to connect to.

termSrvProfile_ImmediateModeOptions_Port.name: termSrvProfile_ImmediateModeOptions_Port
termSrvProfile_ImmediateModeOptions_Port.description: TCP port to which the TELNET or TCP stream is to be redirected to.

termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_StartWith.name: termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_StartWithMenus
termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_StartWith.description: Terminal server interface will start in menu mode when this field is 'yes'.

termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_ToggleScr.name: termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_ToggleScreen
termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_ToggleScr.description: When enabled, users are able to toggle between menu mode and the normal terminal server command line.

termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_RemoteCon.name: termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_RemoteConfiguration
termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_RemoteCon.description: When enabled, the text and host addresses that make up the menu will be retrieved from RADIUS (if RADIUS is enabled).

termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Text1.name: termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Text1
termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Text1.description: The text to put in the terminal server menu for the first login host when remote configuration isn't available.

termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Host1.name: termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Host1
termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Host1.description: The address of the first host to access when terminal server menu mode is being used without remote configuration.

termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Service1.name: termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Service1
termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Service1.description: Type of service required for this selection.

termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Port1.name: termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Port1
termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Port1.description: The port for contacting host. Used only for telnet service.

termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_User1.name: termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_User1
termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_User1.description: The user name for this selection. Used only for rlogin service.

termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Text2.name: termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Text2
termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Text2.description: The text to put in the terminal server menu for the second login host when remote configuration isn't available.

termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Host2.name: termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Host2
termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Host2.description: The address of the second host to access when terminal server menu mode is being used without remote configuration.

termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Service2.name: termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Service2
termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Service2.description: Type of service required for this selection.

termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Port2.name: termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Port2
termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Port2.description: The port for contacting host. Used only for telnet service.

termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_User2.name: termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_User2
termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_User2.description: The user name for this selection. Used only for rlogin service.

termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Text3.name: termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Text3
termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Text3.description: The text to put in the terminal server menu for the third login host when remote configuration isn't available.

termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Host3.name: termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Host3
termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Host3.description: The address of the third host to access when terminal server menu mode is being used without remote configuration.

termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Service3.name: termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Service3
termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Service3.description: Type of service required for this selection.

termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Port3.name: termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Port3
termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Port3.description: The port for contacting host. Used only for telnet service.

termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_User3.name: termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_User3
termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_User3.description: The user name for this selection. Used only for rlogin service.

termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Text4.name: termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Text4
termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Text4.description: The text to put in the terminal server menu for the forth login host when remote configuration isn't available.

termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Host4.name: termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Host4
termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Host4.description: The address of the forth host to access when terminal server menu mode is being used without remote configuration.

termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Service4.name: termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Service4
termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Service4.description: Type of service required for this selection.

termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Port4.name: termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Port4
termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_Port4.description: The port for contacting host. Used only for telnet service.

termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_User4.name: termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_User4
termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_User4.description: The user name for this selection. Used only for rlogin service.

termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_MenuSelec.name: termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_MenuSelectionString
termSrvProfile_MenuModeOptions_MenuSelec.description: The selection string for the menu mode.

termSrvProfile_PppModeConfiguration_Ppp.name: termSrvProfile_PppModeConfiguration_Ppp
termSrvProfile_PppModeConfiguration_Ppp.description: Enable/disable the PPP terminal server command.

termSrvProfile_PppModeConfiguration_Dela.name: termSrvProfile_PppModeConfiguration_Delay
termSrvProfile_PppModeConfiguration_Dela.description: The number of seconds to wait for PPP before putting up the login banner and converting to telnet mode.

termSrvProfile_PppModeConfiguration_Dire.name: termSrvProfile_PppModeConfiguration_Direct
termSrvProfile_PppModeConfiguration_Dire.description: Option defines if PPP negotiation is started directly after 'PPP' Term Server command is received or, not. When disabled, we wait to receive a PPP packet before sending.

termSrvProfile_PppModeConfiguration_Info.name: termSrvProfile_PppModeConfiguration_Info
termSrvProfile_PppModeConfiguration_Info.description: Enable/Disable the PPP/SLIP start up message.

termSrvProfile_SlipModeConfiguration_Sli.name: termSrvProfile_SlipModeConfiguration_Slip
termSrvProfile_SlipModeConfiguration_Sli.description: Enable/disable the SLIP command from the terminal server.

termSrvProfile_SlipModeConfiguration_Sli.name: termSrvProfile_SlipModeConfiguration_SlipBootp
termSrvProfile_SlipModeConfiguration_Sli.description: Enable/disable the SLIP command from the terminal server.

termSrvProfile_SlipModeConfiguration_Inf.name: termSrvProfile_SlipModeConfiguration_Info
termSrvProfile_SlipModeConfiguration_Inf.description: Level of information displayed in SLIP start up message.

termSrvProfile_SlipModeConfiguration_Csl.name: termSrvProfile_SlipModeConfiguration_CslipAutoDetect
termSrvProfile_SlipModeConfiguration_Csl.description: Enable/disbale auto detecting of SLIP header compression. This feature will try to auto-detect if the caller is using Van Jacobson header compression, and if so, the box will automatically switch to CSLIP mode.

termSrvProfile_DialoutConfiguration_Enab.name: termSrvProfile_DialoutConfiguration_Enabled
termSrvProfile_DialoutConfiguration_Enab.description: Allow/disallow modem outdial from the terminal server.

termSrvProfile_DialoutConfiguration_Dire.name: termSrvProfile_DialoutConfiguration_DirectAccess
termSrvProfile_DialoutConfiguration_Dire.description: Allows direct connection to a modem by TELNETing to a configurable modem port.

termSrvProfile_DialoutConfiguration_Port.name: termSrvProfile_DialoutConfiguration_PortForDirectAccess
termSrvProfile_DialoutConfiguration_Port.description: The telnet port number for direct access to a modem.

termSrvProfile_DialoutConfiguration_Pass.name: termSrvProfile_DialoutConfiguration_PasswordForDirectAccess
termSrvProfile_DialoutConfiguration_Pass.description: The password that must be used to gain direct access to a modem

termSrvProfile_DialoutConfiguration_Secu.name: termSrvProfile_DialoutConfiguration_SecurityForDirectAccess
termSrvProfile_DialoutConfiguration_Secu.description: The security method used to control direct modem access.
